nce\": \"I had three very dark years under him, I'd be a coward not to say on behalf of the guys who are back home and did not make it onto the team and that got the darker side of Jurgen.\\\"\", \"from\": 1373, \"to\": 1553, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"three very dark years\", \"from\": 1379, \"to\": 1400}, {\"ngram\": \"a coward\", \"from\": 1419, \"to\": 1427}, {\"ngram\": \"behalf\", \"from\": 1442, \"to\": 1448}, {\"ngram\": \"the guys\", \"from\": 1452, \"to\": 1460}, {\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 1504, \"to\": 1512}, {\"ngram\": \"the darker side\", \"from\": 1526, \"to\": 1541}, {\"ngram\": \"Jurgen\", \"from\": 1545, \"to\": 1551}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Matt Rossiter - part of the unsuccessful men's coxless four who end a 20-year streak of Team GB winning gold in the event also hit out at the 'old guard' of British rowing, who he believed were rooting for them to fail.\", \"from\": 1555, \"to\": 1774, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1643, \"end\": 1650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999996684892, \"rank\": 3.094487202203049e-10, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 1712, \"end\": 1726, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Rowing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British rowing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Rowing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Rowing\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Matt Rossiter - part\", \"from\": 1555, \"to\": 1575}, {\"ngram\": \"the unsuccessful men's coxless\", \"from\": 1579, \"to\": 1609}, {\"ngram\": \"a 20-year streak\", \"from\": 1623, \"to\": 1639}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1659, \"to\": 1663}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 1667, \"to\": 1676}, {\"ngram\": \"the 'old guard\", \"from\": 1693, \"to\": 1707}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The slightly older guard, I'd say, have enjoyed revelling in us not doing so well at the start of the Olympiad,\\\" Rossiter said before the Games.\", \"from\": 1776, \"to\": 1921, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The slightly older guard\", \"from\": 1777, \"to\": 1801}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 1838, \"to\": 1840}, {\"ngram\": \"the start\", \"from\": 1862, \"to\": 1871}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympiad\", \"from\": 1875, \"to\": 1887}, {\"ngram\": \"Rossiter\", \"from\": 1890, \"to\": 1898}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1911, \"to\": 1920}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After their fourth-place finish in the final, he added: \\\"It's more just disappointing that those people will probably be really smug now that they are part of the legacy that won.\", \"from\": 1922, \"to\": 2101, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their fourth-place finish\", \"from\": 1928, \"to\": 1953}, {\"ngram\": \"those people\", \"from\": 2013, \"to\": 2025}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 2073, \"to\": 2077}, {\"ngram\": \"the legacy\", \"from\": 2081, \"to\": 2091}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That was a motivation to do well.\", \"from\": 2102, \"to\": 2135, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a motivation\", \"from\": 2111, \"to\": 2123}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I hope those people are happy we have not continued the gold run.\\\"\", \"from\": 2136, \"to\": 2202, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"those people\", \"from\": 2143, \"to\": 2155}, {\"ngram\": \"the gold run\", \"from\": 2188, \"to\": 2200}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the legendary Redgrave is now convinced that bitterness in the past and adamant that the Brits will sit top of the rowing medal table come the end ofParis 2024.\", \"from\": 2204, \"to\": 2368, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the legendary Redgrave\", \"from\": 2208, \"to\": 2230}, {\"ngram\": \"the past\", \"from\": 2267, \"to\": 2275}, {\"ngram\": \"the Brits\", \"from\": 2293, \"to\": 2302}, {\"ngram\": \"top\", \"from\": 2312, \"to\": 2315}, {\"ngram\": \"the rowing medal table\", \"from\": 2319, \"to\": 2341}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Losing Jurgen Grobler, who had been men's chief coach for a long period of time, and Paul Thompson, the best women's coach, before the Tokyo Games was huge,\\\" said Redgrave.\", \"from\": 2370, \"to\": 2543, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2456, \"end\": 2469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Thompson_(musician)\", \"score\": 0.7338153095888231, \"rank\": 0.10163551401872076, \"text\": \"Paul Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Thompson_(musician)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Thompson_(musician)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Losing Jurgen Grobler\", \"from\": 2371, \"to\": 2392}, {\"ngram\": \"men's chief coach\", \"from\": 2407, \"to\": 2424}, {\"ngram\": \"a long period\", \"from\": 2429, \"to\": 2442}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 2446, \"to\": 2450}, {\"ngram\": \"the best women's coach\", \"from\": 2471, \"to\": 2493}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Games\", \"from\": 2502, \"to\": 2517}, {\"ngram\": \"Redgrave\", \"from\": 2534, \"to\": 2542}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"As an administration we got ourselves a little bit lost.\", \"from\": 2545, \"to\": 2602, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an administration\", \"from\": 2549, \"to\": 2566}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We got so caught up with the politics of change and bringing that change in, which did need to happen.\", \"from\": 2603, \"to\": 2705, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the politics\", \"from\": 2628, \"to\": 2640}, {\"ngram\": \"change\", \"from\": 2644, \"to\": 2650}, {\"ngram\": \"that change\", \"from\": 2664, \"to\": 2675}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We had the quality of athletes and we should have won two gold medals.\", \"from\": 2707, \"to\": 2778, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the quality\", \"from\": 2715, \"to\": 2726}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2730, \"to\": 2738}, {\"ngram\": \"two gold medals\", \"from\": 2762, \"to\": 2777}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That would have been acceptable, but we did not.\", \"from\": 2779, \"to\": 2827, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In that delay (due to Covid) the administration was talking about Paris, and those athletes missed their chance in Tokyo.\\\"\", \"from\": 2828, \"to\": 2950, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2894, \"end\": 2899, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998831299, \"rank\": 1.1705288748114792e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2943, \"end\": 2948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9682059770881086, \"rank\": 0.0328380601233468, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that delay\", \"from\": 2831, \"to\": 2841}, {\"ngram\": \"Covid\", \"from\": 2850, \"to\": 2855}, {\"ngram\": \"the administration\", \"from\": 2857, \"to\": 2875}, {\"ngram\": \"those athletes\", \"from\": 2905, \"to\": 2919}, {\"ngram\": \"their chance\", \"from\": 2927, \"to\": 2939}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GBare sending a 42-strong rowing squadto Paris 2024 with medal prospects littered throughout both male and female categories.\", \"from\": 2952, \"to\": 3082, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2998, \"end\": 3008, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0627238330063873e-15, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Team GBare\", \"from\": 2952, \"